Tuus having taken some notice of the superficies of the land, let us a little search into its bowels. You may divide the subterraneous country into three parts: the metal mines, the caves, and the places of burial.

This land was eminently noted for metal mines, so that “ its stones‚'' in very many places, “ were iron, and out of its hills was digged brana? Dent. viii. 9. From these gain ac- crued to the Jews 3 but to the Christiane, not seldom slavery and misery; being frequently condemned hither by tyrants.
